etic methods to strengthen connections between qualitative researchers’ deep knowledge of their cases and quantitative researchers’ elaboration of cross-case patterns. Packed with useful examples, Redesigning Social Inquiry will be indispensable to experienced professionals and to budding scholars about to embark on their first project.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFuzzy sets. 0aSocial sciencesxResearchxMethodology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  asociety, questions, sociology, sociological, scientist, social, scientific, research, academic, scholarly, study, fieldwork, methods, methodology, graduate, higher education, critique, critical, analysis, causal, variables, theory, theoretical, quantitative, qualitative, data, case, patterns, professional, career, academia, scholars.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226702797423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226702797/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles